page.title: 08Moss Dubs
page.content: Moss Dubs is a man made pond that was constructed in 1982 to attract animals and bird life to the area.Carefully concealed hides have been provided from which it is hoped people will be able to film and watch varied species.In the pond are many fresh water animals such as tadpoles,nymphs, back swimmers,black slug,water bettles,may fly lavae and midge lavae.There are rhododendrons growing on the outskirts of the pond.It is going to take several years before the bird life establishes itself here.But Herons can often be seen along with Mallard Ducks and Coots.
